y for $\\sim 60\\%$ of hot Jupiters with projected obliquities $\\lesssim\n20^\\circ$. Thus $\\sim 20\\%$ of the warm Jupiters and $\\sim 60\\%$ of the hot\nJupiters can be produced by high-eccentricity migration. We also provide\npredictions for the expected mutual inclinations and spin-orbit angles of the\nplanetary systems with hot and warm Jupiters produced by high-eccentricity\nmigration.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 31 Mar 2016 20:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 5 Jul 2016 09:57:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-03"}
