ient way of selecting small AGN and explains our high detection\nfraction (82%) in comparison to comparable surveys. Finally we argue that the\ndetected sources are all likely compact symmetric objects and that none of the\nsources are blazars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Apr 2016 09:12:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-01"}
