anism from those listed above. Taking the decay\n$f_1(1285)\\to f_0(980)\\pi^0 \\to\\pi^+\\pi^-\\pi^0$ as the example, we discuss the\ngeneral approach to the description of the $K\\bar K$ loop mechanism of the\nbreaking of isotopic invariance.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Apr 2016 09:43:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Jun 2016 09:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-29"}
